cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a new method for generating cryptographic keys using pseudorandom decimal sequences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the autocorrelation properties of the generated sequences, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mappings and expansions, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
